headline: Capital One’s Brex Deal And Regulation Put Valuation Gap In Focus
summary: Capital One Financial (NYSE:COF) has agreed to acquire fintech firm Brex in a US$5.15b deal. The acquisition is paired with heightened regulatory attention, including proposed caps on credit card interest rates. Investor legal investigations have begun following a recent period of underperformance and a financial results miss. Capital One is best known for its consumer and small business credit card and banking operations, and Brex brings a technology focused corporate finance platform into...

headline: Interest on new car loans is now tax deductible up to $10,000—here's how much buyers may actually save
summary: A new tax break offers deductions of up to $10,000, but income limits and loan rules mean most buyers will see much smaller savings.

headline: 2 Large-Cap Stocks with Promising Prospects and 1 That Underwhelm
summary: Large-cap stocks usually command their industries because they have the scale to drive market trends. The flip side though is that their sheer size can limit growth as expanding further becomes an increasingly challenging task.
